rkreis zugänglich gemacht werden. Ergänzt wird das Buch mit einem von Peter Weiss verfassten Aufsatz, der hier zum ersten Mal auf Deutsch erscheint.  aPeter Weiss is one of the most important German-language writers of the post-war period. This study sheds new light on his collected works in the context of space and memory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCities and towns in literature. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aBerlin. 4aCultural Studies. 4aErinnerung. 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aGermanistik. 4aHolocaust. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aParis. 4aPeter Weiss. 4aStadt. 4aStockholm. 4aÄsthetik des Widerstands. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aAesthetics of Resistance.  aBerlin.  aCity.  aCultural Studies.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aGerman Literature.  aHolocaust.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMemory Culture.  aMemory.  aParis.  aPeter Weiss.  aStockholm.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839436189zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839436189423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839436189/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  